author: psiwebtn
title: On This Date
text:
On This Date Monday, October 12, 2015 
October 12, 2002 - Marlon Pitts carries 17 times for 163 yards and two touchdowns to lead Pleasant Valley to a 42-6 Mountain Valley Conference win over Pocono Mountain West. Pitts opens the game’s scoring with a 20-yard TD run in the first quarter. He later adds a 62-yard burst to the end zone. Mike Economy collects 106 yards and three touchdowns, scoring on runs of one, four and six yards. The Bears, coached by Neil Dangelo, total 450 yards of offense, including 339 on the ground. PV’s John Carins also adds a 49-yard score.
